A woman in Torquay has been arrested on suspicion of causing or administering a poison or noxious thing with intent to injure, aggrieve or annoy, police say.Devon and Cornwall Police said officers were called to a property on Victoria Road at about 10:00 BST on Sunday. They found an item at the property that was tested by the fire service, which was later confirmed as ammonia hydroxide, police said.A 37-year-old man remains in hospital with injuries believed to be life-changing, they added.
The 31-year-old woman has been released on bail until 18 July.
